    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nbusted doesn't have a good way to retry a test while also doing automatic `after_each` and `before_each` handling.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nTests should be able to explicitly say they want to retry, without having to manually manage the before/after test setup/teardown.\n\n```lua\nit('foo', function()\n  test_retries(2)\nend)\n```\n\nPending pr: https://github.com/lunarmodules/busted/pull/754\n\n## Alternatives\n\nhttps://github.com/lunarmodules/busted/pull/721 shows a way to retry ALL tests indiscriminately: log successes with `--log-success`, then pass that file to `--exclude-names-file` and rerun the test suite.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "test case\n\n```lua\ndescribe('retry test', function()\n  local attempt_count = 0\n\n  before_each(function()\n    attempt_count = attempt_count + 1\n    print(\"Before each for attempt \" .. attempt_count)\n  end)\n\n  after_each(function()\n    print(\"After each for attempt \" .. attempt_count)\n  end)\n\n  it('should succeed on second attempt', function()\n    set_retries(2)  -- 3 total attempts\n    print(\"Running attempt \" .. attempt_count)\n    if attempt_count < 2 then\n      assert.is_true(false, 'Failing attempt ' .. attempt_count)\n    else\n      assert.is_true(true, 'Succeeding on attempt ' .. attempt_count)\n    end\n  end)\nend)\n```",
